<subSubSection pageId="199" pageNumber="478" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="199.[1995,2589,2704,3126]" pageId="199" pageNumber="478">
Taxonomy of A. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1925" box="[2259,2380,2822,2851]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Akodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="199" pageNumber="478" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pervalens">pervalens</taxonomicName>
is poorly explored. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="199" pageNumber="478" type="distribution">
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6707514" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6707514" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6707514/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="199" pageNumber="478" targetBox="[1381,1972,2707,3122]" targetPageId="199">
<paragraph blockId="199.[1995,2589,2704,3126]" pageId="199" pageNumber="478">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1995,2172,2896,2929]" pageId="199" pageNumber="478">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known only from a few localities in Chuquisaca and Tarija departments, SC Bolivia.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="199" pageNumber="478" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="199.[1995,2589,2704,3126]" lastBlockId="199.[1382,2588,3132,3480]" pageId="199" pageNumber="478">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1995,2254,3014,3047]" pageId="199" pageNumber="478">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 116 mm, tail 93 mm, ear 19 mm, hindfoot 25 mm (holotype measurements). No specific data are available for body weight. The Tarija Grass Mouse is a moderately large species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1481,1579,3180,3205]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Akodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="199" pageNumber="478" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Akodon</taxonomicName>
. Dorsum is dark grayish or brownish olive; ventral hairs have dark bases and buffy tips; eye-rings and white spots on chin or throat are absent; and tail is unicolored dark.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="199" pageNumber="478" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="199.[1382,2588,3132,3480]" pageId="199" pageNumber="478">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1383,1494,3290,3323]" pageId="199" pageNumber="478">Habitat.</emphasis>
Humid Yungas forest, Chaco woodland, and semiarid inter-Andean valleys at elevations of 900-2100 m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
